Package model.metaheuristic.util.comparator

This packages contains comparator utility class used by the algorithms or operators.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ConstraintViolationComparator<S>
    Interface to compare constrain violation
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CrowdingDistanceComparator<S extends Solution<?>>
    Compares two solutions according to the crowding distance attribute.
    DominanceComparator<S extends Solution<?>>
    This class implements a solution comparator taking into account the violation constraints.
    EqualSolutionsComparator<S extends Solution<?>>
    This class implements a Comparator (a method for comparing Solution objects) based whether all the objective values are equal or not.
    HypervolumeContributionComparator<S extends Solution<?>>
    Compares two solutions according to the crowding distance attribute.
    ObjectiveComparator<S extends Solution<?>>
    This class implements a comparator based on a given objective
    OverallConstraintViolationComparator<S extends Solution<?>>
    This class implements a Comparator (a method for comparing Solution objects) based on the overall constraint violation of the solutions, as done in NSGA-II.
    RankingAndCrowdingDistanceComparator<S extends Solution<?>>
    This class implements a comparator based on the rank of the solutions; if the rank is the same then the crowding distance is used.
    RankingComparator<S extends Solution<?>>
    This class implements a comparator based on the rank of the solutions.
